<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-19T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="633" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1463a: Circular telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in Latin
                                    America</gloss></hi><note n="2" xml:id="d633fn2">The diplomatic
                                representatives in all Latin American republics except Bolivia and
                                Paraguay.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-19T17:00:00-05:00">October 19, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>All countries having agreed to sign joint telegram to Bolivia and
                            Paraguay, it was signed by the 19 other American countries at 12:30
                            today and sent forward immediately.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>